<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/40: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nouméa</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nouméa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-01T22:00:00+11:00">December
                                    1, 1941—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 2—4:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. Department’s 25, November 29, [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>] 11 p.m.
                            High Commissioner today told me that he awaits confirmation that
                            agreement has been concluded between War Department and Free French
                            delegation at Washington concerning construction and utilization of air
                            bases in New Caledonia. Until this information is received he has
                            instructions not to permit any new work on bases to be undertaken by
                            either the Australians or Americans. He requests that the Hawaiian
                            Department be notified that before taking any action as to sending
                            equipment or personnel he be informed through me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>